review_blob: What a beer should look like, crisp clear nice head!! Not my favorite style but my favorite of the style! The high ABV diffently add's to the beer. Worth the cost? The bottles nice!
Black Liquorice! First taste Ozuo was my second thought!Chewy, malty and chocolate at the end!

Wondeful beer! Nice nose, more clear than cloudy. Nice citrus taste upfront and a little a bittery finish!
Very nice!

One of my favorite! Pours well not much nose, but as you bring it to your mouth the experiance begins! Starts off fruity and then ends with a beautiful chocolate taste that just gets better as it gets warmer. This is Dessert!
Nice Malt and Hops mix. Orange color with tight head. Good beer, nice hot summer session beer!
Expected more from the nose but it wasn't there! Nice head, very carbonated. Spicey/Malty not a lot of anything but many different tastes. Good Drinking!

1999 bottle! Alcohol has mellowed with time and it has aged well. Still nice dry finish but the aroma is not as bursting as the younger bottles but the flavor seems to stay with you longer. Very enjoyable, great way to end the day.

Redish brown, not much hard strong malt taste,roasty, but watery, not much to it.
Not one of their best.

Very good try for a young Brewery! Nice stong hops smell as well as taste. Maybe bananas as well, with a good walming feeling down the throat. Not light or watery holds its taste well. I believe an up and coming brewery!

2003, Nice reddish color leading to a nice tight head. Hops hit you as lift the glass but the fist taste is malt followed by the strong citrus hop and smooth burn. A nice finish to a great Friday night!!

2001 Reddish copper, not overly carbonated, has a lot going on in the mouth. starts of malty sweet and ends with a nice slight sour finish.
I wish I would have waited longer on this one hopefully I'll be able to get some more?
Soft is what comes to mind. Very easy to drink,fruit and honey taste but flat. Different but not bad!
beer_name: Dogfish Head Midas Touch Golden Elixir

review_blob: Beautiful ice cream soda like head, smell the cascade hops overwelms as it reaches your lips! The bitterness stays until it burns out down the back of your throat! I like it!!
Nut Brown and well carbonated, malts and brown sugar, alcohol burn at the finish.Another bottle condition beer I have more hope for this to age well then the 10.
Heavy carbonation,a note of floral and spice and sugar starts ends with a slight alcohol burn. Bottle conditioned hopefully age will do it well!
